&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The meaning of the phrase &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;fortunate in having&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is&amp;nbsp;having or bringing an advantage, an opportunity, a piece of good luck, etc.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;I was &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;fortunate in having&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; a good teacher.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;To&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;will not be used because it should have been followed by the first form of the verb i.e.&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;have&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The sentence contains &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;having&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;after the blank.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is stating that&amp;nbsp;he is fortunate to have a son that is both smart and obedient.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Option 4.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;​Correct sentence:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;You are fortunate &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;in&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; having an intelligent and obedient son.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Let a candle be lit in the memory of the brave martyrs&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Active Voice&lt;/span&gt;, a sentence emphasizes the subject,&amp;nbsp;performing an action.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Passive Voice&lt;/span&gt;, a sentence emphasizes the action or the object of the sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;given sentence&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is in&amp;nbsp;the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;active voice&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When we convert this sentence into&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;passive voice&lt;/span&gt;, the passive format &amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;be + V3 (lit)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;quot; should be used.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;active and passive voice&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;rule&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;for the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;present simple tense&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;option 1&lt;/span&gt;.​&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
