&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;ignorance&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;44px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/images/production/quesImages/quesImage56.png&quot; style=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;164px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Knowledge &lt;/b&gt;means&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;awareness or familiarity gained by experience of a fact or situation.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the meanings of the given words-&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Ignorance&lt;/b&gt; means&amp;nbsp;lack of knowledge or information.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Intelligence &lt;/b&gt;means&amp;nbsp;the ability to acquire and apply knowledge and skills.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Assurance &lt;/b&gt;means&amp;nbsp;a positive declaration intended to give confidence; a promise.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education&lt;/strong&gt; means the process of receiving or giving systematic instruction, especially at a school or university.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hence,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;ignorance&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the correct word.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;many a golfer at this hole.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;There are some sentences that follow a fixed structure, such as &amp;#39;Many&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;Many a&amp;#39;, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Structure&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Many a/an + singular noun + singular verb.
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; Many a student has passed the test.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;golfers&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; needs to be replaced with &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;golfer&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Therefore, the correct sentence is:&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;#39;&lt;em&gt;Disaster has also befallen &lt;strong&gt;many a golfer&amp;nbsp;at this hole.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct answer is option 3 i.e. &amp;#39;to finish&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Option 1 is incorrect as the verb &amp;#39;expected&amp;#39; refers to the past tense and &amp;#39;finishing&amp;#39; is in the present continuous tense and thus cannot be the answer.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Option 4 is incorrect, as it is missing the preposition &amp;#39;to&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus, the correct answer is option 3.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
